					<item>
		<title><![CDATA[Fund Appeal:  Make More Using a Paddle Drop]]></title>
		<link>https://impactauctions.org/2025/02/03/fund-appeal-make-more-using-a-paddle-drop/</link>
		<pubDate>Mon, 03 Feb 2025 15:57:21 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[liveimpactauctions]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://impactauctions.org/?p=5481</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"large"} -->
<p class="has-large-font-size"><strong>A 100-paddle Drop Raffle</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>A 100-paddle raise is a popular fundraising method at gala events, where attendees donate $100 (or a set amount) in exchange for a chance to win a prize, often through a random drawing or selection. The concept works for several reasons:</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":5433,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"media"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://liveimpactauctions.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/img_0808-1.jpg"><img src="https://liveimpactauctions.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/01/img_0808-1.jpg?w=720" alt="" class="wp-image-5433" /></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>1. <strong>Encourages Engagement</strong>: It’s an easy and exciting way for attendees to get involved without committing to a larger donation upfront. The chance to win a prize adds an element of fun and anticipation.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>2. <strong>Quick Fundraising</strong>: This method can raise a significant amount of money in a short period. A large number of participants can quickly contribute, and the overall fundraising goal can be met or exceeded efficiently.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>3. <strong>Accessible Giving</strong>: While high-level donations may be out of reach for some attendees, a $100 contribution is manageable for many, allowing a wider group of people to participate and feel included in the fundraising efforts.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>4. <strong>Prize Incentive</strong>: The added incentive of a prize motivates individuals to donate, as they see the chance for a reward alongside the good cause.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>5. <strong>Creates a Sense of Community</strong>: The collective excitement and participation in the 100-paddle raise foster a sense of shared purpose and involvement among the guests, increasing the event’s overall impact.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>6.&nbsp; <strong>Double Dipping:&nbsp;</strong> It encourages people that have already given a reason to give again. &nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In essence, it combines charity with a fun, community-building element that boosts both engagement and funds for the cause.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Contact<a href="https://www.impactauctions.info"> Impact Auctions</a> today to help plan your next event.  </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:image {"id":5484,"sizeSlug":"large","linkDestination":"media"} -->
<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><a href="https://liveimpactauctions.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/img_2950.png"><img src="https://liveimpactauctions.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/img_2950.png?w=472" alt="" class="wp-image-5484" /></a></figure>
<!-- /wp:image -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
