					<item>
		<title><![CDATA[Puppy Love with Fundraising:  Impact Auctions]]></title>
		<link>https://impactauctions.org/?p=5580</link>
		<pubDate></pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[liveimpactauctions]]></dc:creator>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://impactauctions.org/?p=5580</guid>
		<description></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!-- wp:video {"guid":"5vXo9BIN","id":5526} -->
<figure class="wp-block-video"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
https://videopress.com/v/5vXo9BIN?resizeToParent=true&amp;cover=true&amp;preloadContent=metadata&amp;useAverageColor=true
</div></figure>
<!-- /wp:video -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Auctioning off puppies at a fundraising event can be tricky, but if done ethically and responsibly, it can be a successful way to raise money while ensuring the puppies go to good homes. Here are some key tips:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>1. Prioritize Animal Welfare</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Partner with a reputable breeder or, better yet, a local rescue or shelter.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Ensure all puppies are at least <strong>8 weeks old</strong>, fully vaccinated, and vet-checked.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Provide full documentation on health history, vaccinations, and microchipping.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>2. Screen Potential Bidders</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Advertise the puppy for bidders so they can  do their research. </p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Have an application process to ensure they are ready for pet ownership.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>3. Educate &amp; Promote Responsible Adoption</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Provide information on the breed’s needs, lifespan, and required care.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Have a representative (vet, trainer, or rescue worker) available to answer questions.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Offer post-adoption support, such as free vet check-ups or training sessions.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul class="wp-block-list"><!-- wp:list-item -->
<li>Part of the package should be a puppy training package.  </li>
<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>4.  Ensure a Smooth Transition for the Puppy</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Avoid giving the puppy to the winner <strong>immediately</strong>—arrange a post-event adoption process to confirm they are a good fit.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Offer a refund policy or rehoming guarantee in case of unforeseen issues.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>• Provide a puppy starter kit with food, toys, and a guide to responsible pet ownership.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->]]></content:encoded>
